	   <tr><td colspan=2>A few suggestions to make money below lvl 10. (My friend Athcaldonor did many of these things and was able to make enough money to focus insanely on his smithing skill. He made his first piece of Fine Steel Plate at lvl 12!)<br><br>1) Collect Bonechips (Sell stacks at 2pp, occasionally more)<br>2) Collect spiderling silk and make threads (Needed for high-level smiths to make Fine Steel Plate) Desperate smiths pay A LOT for a stack of these.<br>3) Collect Spider Silk (Swatches normally sell at 1pp a piece)<br>4) Hunt Bears for High Quality bearskins. (This is not the money-maker it used to be, but still)<br>5) Settle down in Kelethin and make small patchwork armor for newbies. You hardly need any tailoring skill to do this, and the patterns and ruined wolf-pelts are right there.<br>6) Ask around, and you will occasionally be able to run errands for high-levellers.<br><br>...And there's lots more. Be imaginative. Just promis me one thing: NEVER run around begging for handouts. The highlevellers you are annoying were in your situation once too, and THEY worked hard to get to where they are now.<br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.povartarewalliance.org/roster/index.shtml?action=preview&charname=Niteklaw&showAlts=false target=_new><b>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka</b></a><br>Brother of the Celestial Fists<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev</td></tr>
